# About xrandr
# RandR ("resize and rotate") is a communications protocol written as an extension to the X11 protocol. 
# XRandR provides the ability to resize, rotate and reflect the root window of a screen. 
# RandR is also responsible for setting the screen refresh rate.
#
# References:
# https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RandR


# To enable HDMI2 output with maximal resolution:
xrandr --output HDMI2 --auto

# To enable HDMI2 output with specific resolution:
xrandr --output HDMI2 --mode 1280x800

# To enable HDMI2 output next to HDMI1 output:
xrandr --output HDMI2 --auto --right-of HDMI1

# To disable HDMI2 output:
xrandr --output HDMI2 --off
